    "content": "During the events of Session XI - The Knight and the Paladin Bahr Reigh is an aasimar paladin and the brother of Gahr. Upon his arrival at Loomlurch, Bahr's loud and boisterous personality contrasts sharply with the rest of the party, leading to some friction. He receives a cupcake from Talia that gives him a halo of fireflies, and he becomes involved in some light-hearted swipes and punches from Kiara and Tarin, although they miss their marks.\r\n\r\nDuring the events of Session XII - The Massacre of Loomlurch Bahr quickly finds himself at odds with Kiara, leading to tension within the group. He summons his horse, Magnificent, or Maggie, although the practicality of navigating the house with a horse is questioned by the party. During the battle, Bahr proves his worth, delivering powerful divine smites against the enemies. However, his infatuation with Skabatha Nightshade distracts him, ultimately leading to his death.\r\n\r\nDuring the events of Session XVI - The Bridge Wedding Bahr Reigh is resurrected by Mr. Witch in exchange for Gahr's departure. Upon his revival, Bahr is quick to rejoin the group, bringing with him his horse, Maggie, and his characteristic flamboyance. His interactions with Lilygrove take on a flirtatious tone, especially after her transformation back to her true form. Bahr’s presence causes tension among the group, particularly with Meela, who remains wary of him. Despite this, Bahr plays a significant role in the group’s battles, especially against the shadows, where his divine smite proves highly effective. He also formally adopts Meela, adding a new layer to his relationship with the group.\r\n\r\nDuring the events of Session XVIII - The Theatre Production Bahr as led by Amidor the Dandelion to the garden in the Palace of the Hearts Desire, where he revived his unconscious friends and found a letter from the Hourglass Coven. Later, he discussed having an open marriage with Lilygrove Thornwhisper, flirted with Endelyn Moongrave as a distraction, and struggled with jealousy after not getting the role he wanted in the play. He also raided previous prisoners' possessions.\r\n\r\nDuring the events of Session XIX - The Wooden Masks Bahr learns of the nature of his brother's death. He tries to apologize to Meela but struggles to make amends, and later performs last rites for fallen goblins.",
